  "text": "We determined the concentration of catecholamines and metabolites by HPLC with electrochemical detection [CITATION_1] using micropunches of the ROI in the flash-frozen hemispheres. We considered n. Ov too small to sample accurately via micropunch, so our samples were limited to CMM, NCM, and MLd. The methods for quantification of catecholamines and metabolites are published elsewhere [CITATION_2] , and we reiterate the relevant portions here. We sectioned the frozen, non-fixed hemispheres at 212uC in the sagittal plane at 300 mm on a cryostat, thaw mounted the sections onto glass slides, and rapidly re-froze them on dry ice. From each of two consecutive sections and using chilled thinwalled stainless steel spring-loaded punch tools (Fine Science Tools, Foster City, CA, USA), we micropunched a region of CMM (0.5 mm i.d.) and of NCM (1 mm i.d.), each for which the anatomical boundaries have been described [CITATION_3] . We also took a micropunch (0.5 mm i.d.) from a region of MLd from two consecutive sections. We expelled the tissue punches into 1.9 ml polypropylene microcentrifuge tubes (one for each punch), froze them on dry ice and stored them at 280uC until assay.",
